00:00:52.980 --> 00:00:54.630
JOSH LANZET: I believe that.

00:00:54.630 --> 00:00:56.627
So let's get to-- let's
jump right in to that.

00:00:56.627 --> 00:00:57.210
What was that?

00:00:57.210 --> 00:01:00.420
A really boring drama, I think
that's what that was, right?

00:01:00.420 --> 00:01:02.032
No action at all.

00:01:02.032 --> 00:01:03.240
Let's start at the beginning.

00:01:03.240 --> 00:01:04.615
Can you guys talk
me through kind

00:01:04.615 --> 00:01:06.990
of the origins of this show?

00:01:06.990 --> 00:01:09.030
How you guys came up with
it, how it came to be.

00:01:09.030 --> 00:01:11.010
STEVEN SCAIA: Well it all
started because Matt and I,

00:01:11.010 --> 00:01:13.020
we've been writing together
for quite some time.

00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:16.080
And nearly every
development season, we

00:01:16.080 --> 00:01:18.240
write a treasure hunter script.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:21.223
And I think-- is this our
fourth or fifth crack at that?

00:01:21.223 --> 00:01:22.890
MATTHEW FEDERMAN:
This is the fifth one,

00:01:22.890 --> 00:01:24.030
and it's actually getting made.

00:01:24.030 --> 00:01:24.863
STEVEN SCAIA: Right.

00:01:24.863 --> 00:01:28.950
And so the difference
this time for us was we

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:33.210
discovered that ISIS's
second best form of revenue

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:35.317
was looting antiquities
and selling them

00:01:35.317 --> 00:01:36.150
on the black market.

00:01:36.150 --> 00:01:37.110
JOSH LANZET: Wow.

00:01:37.110 --> 00:01:38.485
STEVEN SCAIA: And
so that gave us

00:01:38.485 --> 00:01:42.822
a really good modern way in
to giving stakes to treasure.

00:01:42.822 --> 00:01:45.030
When you don't have Nazis
and an Ark of the Covenant,

00:01:45.030 --> 00:01:46.450
you've got to find a new way.

00:01:46.450 --> 00:01:49.290
And that was a nice fresh take
and a way in that still had

00:01:49.290 --> 00:01:51.290
very modern resonance, I think.

00:01:51.290 --> 00:01:52.290
JOSH LANZET: Oh my gosh.

00:01:52.290 --> 00:01:54.450
So you said, Nazis,
Ark of the Covenant.

00:01:54.450 --> 00:01:57.600
So I have to ask,
having watched this.

00:01:57.600 --> 00:01:59.070
Very Indiana Jones.

00:01:59.070 --> 00:02:00.293
Very "Romancing the Stone."

00:02:00.293 --> 00:02:01.710
Were those influences
for you guys

00:02:01.710 --> 00:02:02.730
when you were writing this?

00:02:02.730 --> 00:02:03.490
STEVEN SCAIA: Absolutely.

00:02:03.490 --> 00:02:04.410
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: Yeah
I mean, and it also

00:02:04.410 --> 00:02:07.130
takes place in a world where
people have seen those things.

00:02:07.130 --> 00:02:09.247
So they are
referenced because we

00:02:09.247 --> 00:02:10.830
feel like it would
be weird for people

00:02:10.830 --> 00:02:14.220
to be on a treasure
hunt in 2019 and not

00:02:14.220 --> 00:02:16.798
be talking about Indiana
Jones all the time.

00:02:16.798 --> 00:02:18.840
JOSH LANZET: I can just
imagine them being there,

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:21.937
being like, yeah,
this is like a movie.

00:02:21.937 --> 00:02:23.270
I don't know what it was called.

00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:23.970
Anyway.

00:02:23.970 --> 00:02:25.260
Yeah, that would be--

00:02:25.260 --> 00:02:27.348
that would be very, very odd.

00:02:27.348 --> 00:02:28.140
But I think those--

00:02:28.140 --> 00:02:29.550
I mean, we're talking
about movies right now.

00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:31.170
We're not talking
about television.

00:02:31.170 --> 00:02:34.670
This felt-- I know you guys
haven't watched the full show.

00:02:34.670 --> 00:02:37.170
But you saw in the trailer, I
mean, it feels very cinematic.

00:02:37.170 --> 00:02:39.000
Did you guys set out
to make something

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:41.515
that was a little more
movie-ish than TV?

00:02:41.515 --> 00:02:43.140
STEVEN SCAIA: I think
for us, you know,

00:02:43.140 --> 00:02:47.190
we've always been big
idea, very visual writers.

00:02:47.190 --> 00:02:50.670
And when CBS wanted to do
a summer blockbuster on TV,

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:52.590
we were more than happy
to take them up on it.

00:02:52.590 --> 00:02:54.507
And do something maybe
even a little different

00:02:54.507 --> 00:02:56.340
for them that they were
excited about where

00:02:56.340 --> 00:02:57.810
we didn't shoot in Atlanta.

00:02:57.810 --> 00:02:59.892
We shot all over
the world instead.

00:02:59.892 --> 00:03:02.350
And I think one of the things
we really like about the show

00:03:02.350 --> 00:03:03.892
and what was really
fun with you guys

00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:06.100
was, we went to those places.

00:03:06.100 --> 00:03:07.633
We basically did our own stunts.

00:03:07.633 --> 00:03:09.300
And we basically
didn't use green screen

00:03:09.300 --> 00:03:11.717
unless we were maybe putting
a mountain in the background.

00:03:11.717 --> 00:03:13.980
But anytime someone comes
through a skylight or rides

00:03:13.980 --> 00:03:16.450
a motorcycle, that's a real
person doing the real thing.

00:03:16.450 --> 00:03:19.680
It's not digital anything.

00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:20.460
And it just--

00:03:20.460 --> 00:03:22.110
I think you can
tell in the show,

00:03:22.110 --> 00:03:23.590
it feels like a real adventure.

00:03:23.590 --> 00:03:24.270
SOFIA PERNAS: Yeah
and how we were

00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:26.130
able to shoot in
some of these places.

00:03:26.130 --> 00:03:27.577
Like, you saw the
Trevi Fountain.

00:03:27.577 --> 00:03:29.160
And we were right
outside the Vatican.

00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:30.180
And I think it
was you, Matt, who

00:03:30.180 --> 00:03:32.280
was like, I didn't even think
we would be able to do that.

00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:33.630
I thought we'd have
to green screen that.

00:03:33.630 --> 00:03:35.223
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: It's really
funny because when we--

00:03:35.223 --> 00:03:35.870
is this on, or not?

00:03:35.870 --> 00:03:36.150
I can't tell.

00:03:36.150 --> 00:03:37.100
JOSH LANZET: I think it is.

00:03:37.100 --> 00:03:37.220
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: OK.

00:03:37.220 --> 00:03:38.000
SOFIA PERNAS: Just have to--

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:39.292
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: I've got to--

00:03:39.292 --> 00:03:40.230
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:03:40.230 --> 00:03:42.188
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: When
we'd written that, which

00:03:42.188 --> 00:03:43.890
was in 2016 at this point.

00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:46.477
And we just wrote like, oh, we
should say something specific

00:03:46.477 --> 00:03:47.310
that they walk past.

00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:50.700
And then like, in some universe,
at least people will imagine

00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:51.827
where they are in Italy.

00:03:51.827 --> 00:03:53.910
But we're just clearly
never going to shoot there.

00:03:53.910 --> 00:03:56.550
And then, everything about
this project just kept being us

00:03:56.550 --> 00:03:58.860
saying, well they're
never going to do this.

00:03:58.860 --> 00:04:02.760
But we might as well have
fun and just push it anyway.

00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:04.260
And then like,
see if someone is,

00:04:04.260 --> 00:04:06.160
you know, somehow dumb enough
to take us up on this thing.

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:06.810
STEVEN SCAIA: It's
the first project

00:04:06.810 --> 00:04:09.473
we've worked on where it got
bigger and bigger and bigger

00:04:09.473 --> 00:04:10.140
as you go along.

00:04:10.140 --> 00:04:13.410
Because part of the
magic of television is,

00:04:13.410 --> 00:04:15.820
do it faster and
spend less every time.

00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:18.550
And everything we
came up with, it just

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:20.550
would keep getting larger
and larger and larger.

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:22.785
We weren't-- we weren't
originally going to Morocco.

00:04:22.785 --> 00:04:24.160
Then all of a
sudden it was like,

00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:26.370
hey how about Morocco
as well as Italy?

00:04:26.370 --> 00:04:27.852
And then when we
got to Morocco, we

00:04:27.852 --> 00:04:30.060
decided, hey, how about we
go to an whole other place

00:04:30.060 --> 00:04:30.593
in Morocco?

00:04:30.593 --> 00:04:32.760
Because it's got a completely
different visual feel.

00:04:32.760 --> 00:04:35.340
And then it went from
foot chase to car chase.

00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:37.170
And like, all
these little things

00:04:37.170 --> 00:04:39.420
we would do along the way
when these guys were totally

00:04:39.420 --> 00:04:41.470
game where they wanted
to crank it up too.

00:04:41.470 --> 00:04:42.970
MATT BARR: Yeah,
and you know, there

00:04:42.970 --> 00:04:44.762
was-- you would read
the scripts and think,

00:04:44.762 --> 00:04:48.090
there is no way we can do this.

00:04:48.090 --> 00:04:50.640
So you know-- and when
we'd arrive on set

00:04:50.640 --> 00:04:53.715
and there was live cobras or
there was a zip line that's

00:04:53.715 --> 00:04:56.090
going to catch on fire and
the whole half of the building

00:04:56.090 --> 00:04:57.960
is going to fall
over, or, you know,

00:04:57.960 --> 00:04:59.860
I'm going to be tied
to the top of a BMW.

00:04:59.860 --> 00:05:00.990
And we would do it.

00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:03.837
It was like, somehow these
guys and our whole team--

00:05:03.837 --> 00:05:05.420
STEVEN SCAIA: I want
to feel like it's

00:05:05.420 --> 00:05:07.350
because we were far enough
away from CBS headquarters

00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:08.970
that they didn't quite
know what we were up to.

00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:09.330
MATT BARR: No that's exact--

00:05:09.330 --> 00:05:11.530
cause, yeah, when you're in the,
you know, the heart of Morocco,

00:05:11.530 --> 00:05:12.230
you can get away with shit.

00:05:12.230 --> 00:05:14.105
SOFIA PERNAS: Yeah, Barr
broke both his legs.

00:05:14.105 --> 00:05:15.658
We have no idea how it happened.

00:05:15.658 --> 00:05:16.825
We're going to make it work.

00:05:16.825 --> 00:05:17.616
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah.

00:05:17.616 --> 00:05:19.440
MATT BARR: It was a
real cobra, you guys.

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:20.850
JOSH LANZET: I feel like
for the two of you, I mean,

00:05:20.850 --> 00:05:22.350
you guys are probably
having scripts

00:05:22.350 --> 00:05:23.760
sent to you all the time.

00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:26.160
What was your initial
reaction when you read this?

00:05:26.160 --> 00:05:28.475
I mean, this had to
have been crazy, right?

00:05:28.475 --> 00:05:29.850
MATT BARR: I'll
take a step back.

00:05:29.850 --> 00:05:32.490
I remember the press release
for this in like, 2017.

00:05:32.490 --> 00:05:36.240
And there was like, CBS buys
series, "Blood and Treasure."

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:38.160
And I was like, oh my god.

00:05:38.160 --> 00:05:40.810
That's going to be the
greatest show ever.

00:05:40.810 --> 00:05:42.690
We were both doing other
shows at that time.

00:05:42.690 --> 00:05:44.970
But, yeah.

00:05:44.970 --> 00:05:46.220
I remember reading the script.

00:05:46.220 --> 00:05:48.260
And as a boy that grew
up like every boy that

00:05:48.260 --> 00:05:52.540
wants to be Indiana Jones,
and I thought, I'll be damned.

00:05:52.540 --> 00:05:53.040
They did it.

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:54.710
Like, however they've
kind of captured

00:05:54.710 --> 00:05:58.070
that magic, which I don't
know why no one seems to--

00:05:58.070 --> 00:05:59.008
no one has done this.

00:05:59.008 --> 00:05:59.550
I don't know.

00:05:59.550 --> 00:05:59.830
It's like--

00:05:59.830 --> 00:06:02.288
SOFIA PERNAS: Yeah well we both
have crazy casting stories.

00:06:02.288 --> 00:06:03.950
Because specifically
because we both

00:06:03.950 --> 00:06:05.300
fell in love with the script.

00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:07.490
And so yes, I was on another
show at the same time.

00:06:07.490 --> 00:06:10.490
But I was like, now I'm
getting on this show.

00:06:10.490 --> 00:06:11.280
It's happening.

00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:12.020
JOSH LANZET: Is
that how that works?

00:06:12.020 --> 00:06:13.562
Is that you just
say, I'm getting on?

00:06:13.562 --> 00:06:16.025
SOFIA PERNAS: I don't
care what I got to do.

00:06:16.025 --> 00:06:17.400
MATT BARR: Who do
I have to kill?

00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:19.820
SOFIA PERNAS: Who
do I have to kill?

00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.495
Yeah, but it was nuts.

00:06:21.495 --> 00:06:22.370
I mean, I think what?

00:06:22.370 --> 00:06:25.060
You had 24 hours, then
you got on a plane.

00:06:25.060 --> 00:06:26.380
And you were in--

00:06:26.380 --> 00:06:27.360
you were in Montreal.

00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:27.830
MATT BARR: Yeah.

00:06:27.830 --> 00:06:29.705
STEVEN SCAIA: My two
favorite casting stories

00:06:29.705 --> 00:06:32.790
are when she came in
to read for the part,

00:06:32.790 --> 00:06:34.880
well she has an English
accent on the show.

00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:37.220
And she came in, did the
whole thing, and left.

00:06:37.220 --> 00:06:39.870
And we were like, was that?

00:06:39.870 --> 00:06:40.730
Is she English?

00:06:40.730 --> 00:06:43.967
This doesn't-- like, we had
no idea whether it was a put

00:06:43.967 --> 00:06:45.050
on or whether it was real.

00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:46.758
Because you stayed in
it the entire time.

00:06:46.758 --> 00:06:47.510
It was brilliant.

00:06:47.510 --> 00:06:50.240
SOFIA PERNAS: First of all,
I don't remember doing that.

00:06:50.240 --> 00:06:51.390
I don't remember.

00:06:51.390 --> 00:06:52.808
STEVEN SCAIA: You don't
remember not doing it either.

00:06:52.808 --> 00:06:53.804
SOFIA PERNAS: I don't
remember not doing it either.

00:06:53.804 --> 00:06:54.387
So, who knows?

00:06:54.387 --> 00:06:55.846
MATT BARR: She
actually is English.

00:06:55.846 --> 00:06:56.815
This is all an act.

00:06:56.815 --> 00:06:58.190
STEVEN SCAIA: But
then, then when

00:06:58.190 --> 00:07:01.240
we called this guy to tell
him he got the job, you could,

00:07:01.240 --> 00:07:04.460
like, the scream was so
loud that the phone actually

00:07:04.460 --> 00:07:05.360
shorted out.

00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:07.190
And then it stopped.

00:07:07.190 --> 00:07:08.420
And he's like, OK guys.

00:07:08.420 --> 00:07:08.960
What do I need to do?

00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:10.350
And we're like,
don't worry about it.

00:07:10.350 --> 00:07:11.360
We just need you to get
on a plane tomorrow.

00:07:11.360 --> 00:07:12.512
And he's like, ha ha ha.

00:07:12.512 --> 00:07:13.970
No seriously, when
do I need to go?

00:07:13.970 --> 00:07:15.410
We're like, no Matt.

00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:16.880
We start shooting on Wednesday.

00:07:16.880 --> 00:07:19.180
Then it got really quiet.

00:07:19.180 --> 00:07:20.670
MATT BARR: Pack
for seven months.

00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:21.500
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah.

00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:22.460
JOSH LANZET: So you
packed for seven months

00:07:22.460 --> 00:07:24.110
in less than 12 hours?

00:07:24.110 --> 00:07:25.250
MATT BARR: I really did.

00:07:25.250 --> 00:07:25.760
JOSH LANZET: Oh my--

00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:26.540
SOFIA PERNAS: Like, I'll
just buy my closet--

00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:28.165
MATT BARR: The good
thing is, you know,

00:07:28.165 --> 00:07:30.290
I probably own three jeans
and a few t-shirts and--

00:07:30.290 --> 00:07:32.082
JOSH LANZET: A lot of
linen and flip flops.

00:07:32.082 --> 00:07:34.340
MATT BARR: Yeah, a couple
flip-flops and, you know,

00:07:34.340 --> 00:07:35.220
I'm good to go.

00:07:35.220 --> 00:07:36.440
JOSH LANZET: So you can
take the boy out of Texas.

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:37.550
That's pretty much
what you're saying.

00:07:37.550 --> 00:07:38.060
MATT BARR: That's right.

00:07:38.060 --> 00:07:38.893
JOSH LANZET: Got it.

00:07:38.893 --> 00:07:39.685
So, so OK.

00:07:39.685 --> 00:07:41.060
So you guys, you
got the scripts.

00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:43.070
I mean, was it a very
long process for you

00:07:43.070 --> 00:07:44.930
two, kind of starting
from reading it

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:46.460
to being cast in this?

00:07:49.170 --> 00:07:51.975
SOFIA PERNAS: Well, what
made mine a little bit crazy

00:07:51.975 --> 00:07:54.007
was because I was on
another show at the time.

00:07:54.007 --> 00:07:54.840
JOSH LANZET: Oh wow.

00:07:54.840 --> 00:07:58.410
SOFIA PERNAS: And so it was
a very interesting needle

00:07:58.410 --> 00:08:00.643
to thread, that one.

00:08:00.643 --> 00:08:03.060
JOSH LANZET: I'm sensing some
withholding, which is great.

00:08:03.060 --> 00:08:03.940
I'm fine with it.

00:08:03.940 --> 00:08:05.580
STEVEN SCAIA: I think it's
that we all knew she was cast

00:08:05.580 --> 00:08:06.663
and she knew she was cast.

00:08:06.663 --> 00:08:08.803
But the world could not
know she was cast yet.

00:08:08.803 --> 00:08:10.470
Until the fate of
that show was decided.

00:08:10.470 --> 00:08:12.270
SOFIA PERNAS: Yes, the fate
of the show had to be decided.

00:08:12.270 --> 00:08:13.200
STEVEN SCAIA: And we
had contingency plans.

00:08:13.200 --> 00:08:14.010
But still.

00:08:14.010 --> 00:08:14.310
SOFIA PERNAS: Yeah.

00:08:14.310 --> 00:08:14.690
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah.

00:08:14.690 --> 00:08:16.273
MATTHEW FEDERMAN:
Our contingency plan

00:08:16.273 --> 00:08:17.805
was to end that other show.

00:08:17.805 --> 00:08:19.680
We were like, she's
literally the only person

00:08:19.680 --> 00:08:21.138
in the world that
can do this part.

00:08:21.138 --> 00:08:23.490
So whatever we have to do,
whoever we have to kill,

00:08:23.490 --> 00:08:24.445
just let us know.

00:08:24.445 --> 00:08:26.070
MATT BARR: What I'll
say is pretty cool

00:08:26.070 --> 00:08:29.930
is like, it's rare when you
read a script that you just love

00:08:29.930 --> 00:08:31.680
and you think, I'm
born to play this part.

00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:35.350
And very rarely does that
align with your reality.

00:08:35.350 --> 00:08:38.293
And when it does, it's like
a freaking miracle, you know?

00:08:38.293 --> 00:08:39.960
So it was fun that
when this worked out,

00:08:39.960 --> 00:08:42.870
and I joined this team,
that thought I'm like,

00:08:42.870 --> 00:08:44.162
walking in my dreams right now.

00:08:44.162 --> 00:08:46.703
STEVEN SCAIA: And I think that
that's what's great about them

00:08:46.703 --> 00:08:49.260
in the show is, we cast them
as actors to play parts.

00:08:49.260 --> 00:08:52.860
But you guys are so very
much those people on screen

00:08:52.860 --> 00:08:54.840
that we wrote before
we even met you.

00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:58.110
You guys are the perfect
people for those roles.

00:08:58.110 --> 00:09:00.743
Because there are so many
times we'd be somewhere,

00:09:00.743 --> 00:09:02.160
and you would say
or do something,

00:09:02.160 --> 00:09:03.020
or you would say
or do something.

00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:04.920
And we're like, that's
such a Lexi thing.

00:09:04.920 --> 00:09:06.180
So Lexi.

00:09:06.180 --> 00:09:08.928
It's so Danny.

00:09:08.928 --> 00:09:10.970
JOSH LANZET: Well so when
did you two first meet?

00:09:10.970 --> 00:09:11.803
Did you meet on set?

00:09:11.803 --> 00:09:14.530
Or did you have a
chemistry read beforehand?

00:09:14.530 --> 00:09:18.180
SOFIA PERNAS: Well, technically,
we had met January of 2018.

00:09:18.180 --> 00:09:20.390
Because we were both on
military shows at the time.

00:09:20.390 --> 00:09:21.340
MATT BARR: At a veteran's event.

00:09:21.340 --> 00:09:22.140
SOFIA PERNAS: We met
at a veteran awards

00:09:22.140 --> 00:09:24.360
ceremony promoting each
other's military shows.

00:09:24.360 --> 00:09:26.810
Then six months
later, we were doing--

00:09:26.810 --> 00:09:30.240
he calls me and he
goes, hey, we met.

00:09:30.240 --> 00:09:32.130
And I'm chemistry reading
with you tomorrow.

00:09:32.130 --> 00:09:33.675
And I was like, oh no sh--

00:09:33.675 --> 00:09:35.272
no shit.

00:09:35.272 --> 00:09:37.230
JOSH LANZET: My favorite
thing is, you said it.

00:09:37.230 --> 00:09:38.400
Then you looked around.

00:09:38.400 --> 00:09:39.990
And then you said it again.

00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:41.790
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: That was peak
Sofia you just saw right there.

00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:43.150
That's why she's so Lexi.

00:09:43.150 --> 00:09:45.873
MATT BARR: It's cool cause
at that veteran's event--

00:09:45.873 --> 00:09:47.290
at that event when
I met Sofia, we

00:09:47.290 --> 00:09:49.628
were both doing
this veterans thing.

00:09:49.628 --> 00:09:52.170
I remember thinking like, this
is the kind of actress I like.

00:09:52.170 --> 00:09:53.640
One, what a cool human being.

00:09:53.640 --> 00:09:55.430
But two, we talked
about work and sort

00:09:55.430 --> 00:09:56.880
of how we approached
being actors.

00:09:56.880 --> 00:09:59.640
And I was like, this
is the perfect balance.

00:09:59.640 --> 00:10:01.620
Like, I would love
to get in a foxhole

00:10:01.620 --> 00:10:03.400
with an actor like this.

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:05.710
And so we, you know, just
thought, good luck to you,

00:10:05.710 --> 00:10:06.210
you know?

00:10:06.210 --> 00:10:07.960
And I hope I get to
work with you one day.

00:10:07.960 --> 00:10:09.810
And then three months
later, we were--

00:10:09.810 --> 00:10:10.890
SOFIA PERNAS: We were
literally in a foxhole.

00:10:10.890 --> 00:10:11.680
Yeah.

00:10:11.680 --> 00:10:13.410
MATT BARR: Literally
in a burning--

00:10:13.410 --> 00:10:14.248
burning foxhole.

00:10:14.248 --> 00:10:16.290
JOSH LANZET: I mean, I
haven't seen that episode.

00:10:16.290 --> 00:10:17.550
But I can't wait.

00:10:17.550 --> 00:10:19.260
It sounds great.

00:10:19.260 --> 00:10:23.040
So this show jumps everywhere,
all over geographically,

00:10:23.040 --> 00:10:23.832
all over the world.

00:10:23.832 --> 00:10:25.207
When you two were
writing it, was

00:10:25.207 --> 00:10:26.940
part of the allure
to essentially take

00:10:26.940 --> 00:10:29.587
the audience on a free trip
with you all around the world?

00:10:29.587 --> 00:10:31.920
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: Yeah because
I-- lots of times the way

00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:34.805
we split it up is Steve is
running the set, basically,

00:10:34.805 --> 00:10:36.180
and I'm running
the writers room.

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:37.307
And then we kind of cross--

00:10:37.307 --> 00:10:37.890
we cross over.

00:10:37.890 --> 00:10:39.845
And sometimes I would
be in the writers room

00:10:39.845 --> 00:10:41.220
and we'd be working
on the story.

00:10:41.220 --> 00:10:42.840
And then Steve would come in
and we would pitch him a thing.

00:10:42.840 --> 00:10:44.310
And he'd be like, wait, where?

00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:45.630
We're just in like, one city?

00:10:45.630 --> 00:10:47.130
And I'm like, well we're
figuring out the story.

00:10:47.130 --> 00:10:47.370
No no.

00:10:47.370 --> 00:10:48.950
We got to-- we got
to-- we got to go here.

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:49.975
We'll go to-- we'll
go to Montreal here,

00:10:49.975 --> 00:10:50.450
and we'll go to here.

00:10:50.450 --> 00:10:51.920
You know, he just like,
starts throwing cities up

00:10:51.920 --> 00:10:52.462
on the board.

00:10:52.462 --> 00:10:53.130
I'm like, OK.

00:10:53.130 --> 00:10:55.213
Get out of the room until
we figure out the story.

00:10:55.213 --> 00:10:58.230
But it was definitely
the point was that it

00:10:58.230 --> 00:10:59.490
should feel like a travelogue.

00:10:59.490 --> 00:11:01.567
We would joke, it's
Anthony Bourdain with guns.

00:11:01.567 --> 00:11:03.900
But it's like, it should feel
like these beautiful parts

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:04.800
of the world.

00:11:04.800 --> 00:11:07.905
And the audience
is on an adventure,

00:11:07.905 --> 00:11:10.560
you know, as much with
us as the characters.

00:11:10.560 --> 00:11:12.190
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah,
I think for us,

00:11:12.190 --> 00:11:13.440
we've always loved traveling.

00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:15.390
And so to be able
to-- for us to be

00:11:15.390 --> 00:11:18.030
able to go and see these places,
but also present them in a way

00:11:18.030 --> 00:11:20.140
that you would want
to go to them too.

00:11:20.140 --> 00:11:23.680
And so, when we go
to a refugee camp,

00:11:23.680 --> 00:11:25.300
it's a sexy refugee
camp by the beach.

00:11:25.300 --> 00:11:25.800
You know?

00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:28.320
Like, you really get
the sense of this

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:30.780
is a world that you want to
get out there and explore.

00:11:30.780 --> 00:11:33.000
And I think for us,
one of the fun things

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:35.790
was finding those places
in Morocco and Italy.

00:11:35.790 --> 00:11:38.800
I mean, Italy's easy because,
I mean, look at that.

00:11:38.800 --> 00:11:40.050
Who wouldn't want to go there?

00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:41.675
But there's so many
places in the world

00:11:41.675 --> 00:11:43.398
that you wouldn't
necessarily think of,

00:11:43.398 --> 00:11:44.940
this would be a
great place to visit.

00:11:44.940 --> 00:11:46.790
But you go and we show that.

00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:48.540
And I think hopefully
it'll get people out

00:11:48.540 --> 00:11:50.180
of their houses a
little bit more.

00:11:50.180 --> 00:11:50.520
JOSH LANZET: Ah.

00:11:50.520 --> 00:11:52.145
So you were trying
to encourage travel?

00:11:52.145 --> 00:11:52.660
I get it.

00:11:52.660 --> 00:11:53.220
That makes sense.

00:11:53.220 --> 00:11:54.550
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: We're
actually a travel agency

00:11:54.550 --> 00:11:55.920
that's, you know, working
the long way around

00:11:55.920 --> 00:11:56.540
on our business.

00:11:56.540 --> 00:11:56.970
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah.

00:11:56.970 --> 00:11:57.970
JOSH LANZET: Oh perfect.

00:11:57.970 --> 00:11:58.680
Well I'm sold.

00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:02.403
I'm ready to go wherever
that picture was taken.

00:12:02.403 --> 00:12:03.570
This was filmed across what?

00:12:03.570 --> 00:12:04.350
Three continents?

00:12:04.350 --> 00:12:04.830
Is that right?

00:12:04.830 --> 00:12:05.860
STEVEN SCAIA: That's true.

00:12:05.860 --> 00:12:07.650
JOSH LANZET: So what was it like
for-- have you guys ever been

00:12:07.650 --> 00:12:09.180
on shows where you were
traveling as much as you

00:12:09.180 --> 00:12:10.260
traveled for this?

00:12:10.260 --> 00:12:12.060
MATT BARR: No.

00:12:12.060 --> 00:12:13.110
It was awesome.

00:12:13.110 --> 00:12:14.333
SOFIA PERNAS: It was nuts.

00:12:14.333 --> 00:12:15.000
MATT BARR: Yeah.

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:18.960
It was fun to, like, go to
sleep in the Italian Alps,

00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:21.350
and then wake up in Morocco.

00:12:21.350 --> 00:12:23.547
And you're in some
Medina with camels.

00:12:23.547 --> 00:12:25.380
JOSH LANZET: I hope you
know that no one can

00:12:25.380 --> 00:12:26.200
say that sentence.

00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:28.200
Like there are like, maybe
five people that have

00:12:28.200 --> 00:12:29.220
said that sentence before.

00:12:29.220 --> 00:12:31.140
STEVEN SCAIA: I've never had
a job where the call to prayer

00:12:31.140 --> 00:12:32.820
was my alarm in the morning.

00:12:32.820 --> 00:12:34.140
And that was pretty special.

00:12:34.140 --> 00:12:34.500
SOFIA PERNAS: Yup.

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:35.250
MATT BARR: Yeah.

00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:36.042
SOFIA PERNAS: Yeah.

00:12:36.042 --> 00:12:37.110
It was-- I'm from--

00:12:37.110 --> 00:12:38.290
I was born in Morocco.

00:12:38.290 --> 00:12:42.270
So I've now had the honor of
twice in a row shooting there.

00:12:42.270 --> 00:12:46.050
But this one was like,
very, we shot all over.

00:12:46.050 --> 00:12:46.980
So it was great.

00:12:46.980 --> 00:12:48.610
I was like the secret
Moroccan on set.

00:12:48.610 --> 00:12:52.100
Because apparently I don't look
Moroccan, is what I was told.

00:12:52.100 --> 00:12:52.360
MATTHEW FEDERMAN:
That's a weird--

00:12:52.360 --> 00:12:53.620
SOFIA PERNAS: Cause
I speak the language.

00:12:53.620 --> 00:12:55.240
JOSH LANZET: I was going to
say, that's a new script,

00:12:55.240 --> 00:12:56.032
is Secret Moroccan.

00:12:56.032 --> 00:12:57.282
SOFIA PERNAS: Secret Moroccan.

00:12:57.282 --> 00:12:59.140
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: Can
you find the Moroccan?

00:12:59.140 --> 00:13:00.932
JOSH LANZET: It's like
a new Where's Waldo?

00:13:00.932 --> 00:13:01.793
I'm excited.

00:13:01.793 --> 00:13:04.210
Was the travel-- I imagine
travel might be a little easier

00:13:04.210 --> 00:13:05.918
for you because you
speak, I want to say,

00:13:05.918 --> 00:13:06.980
is it four languages?

00:13:06.980 --> 00:13:07.480
Yeah.

00:13:07.480 --> 00:13:09.022
So it might have
been easier for you.

00:13:09.022 --> 00:13:11.970
And Matt, I think
you're cracking one?

00:13:11.970 --> 00:13:13.270
MATT BARR: That's right.

00:13:13.270 --> 00:13:14.920
JOSH LANZET: It's like--

00:13:14.920 --> 00:13:15.700
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: He's
got a couple more classes.

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:17.367
And then he's totally
going to be there.

00:13:17.367 --> 00:13:19.720
MATT BARR: Sofia's dad
won the Nobel Peace Prize.

00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:22.170
Matt's dad mows the
yard on Sundays.

00:13:22.170 --> 00:13:23.920
JOSH LANZET: You know,
and mowing the yard

00:13:23.920 --> 00:13:25.702
is a peaceful thing
that deserves a prize.

00:13:25.702 --> 00:13:27.160
STEVEN SCAIA: And
he's great at it.

00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:28.993
MATT BARR: Yeah, but
he's great at it, guys.

00:13:28.993 --> 00:13:32.080
STEVEN SCAIA: He like, puts
the pattern on it, you know?

00:13:32.080 --> 00:13:33.400
JOSH LANZET: I've always been
impressed with your father.

00:13:33.400 --> 00:13:34.400
I want you to know that.

00:13:34.400 --> 00:13:35.395
MATT BARR: Thank you.

00:13:35.395 --> 00:13:37.270
JOSH LANZET: But in
terms of all this travel,

00:13:37.270 --> 00:13:39.370
I imagine some things
didn't go as planned, right?

00:13:39.370 --> 00:13:40.510
There had to have been--

00:13:40.510 --> 00:13:42.400
nothing ever goes
perfectly, especially when

00:13:42.400 --> 00:13:44.320
you're running three
continents in the mix.

00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:47.478
Any stories of things that
kind of didn't go so hot?

00:13:47.478 --> 00:13:49.770
STEVEN SCAIA: I mean, the
two stories that come to mind

00:13:49.770 --> 00:13:51.960
are Colosseum Night.

00:13:51.960 --> 00:13:54.810
And then the day in
the Medina in Tangier.

00:13:54.810 --> 00:13:58.170
Where we were
shooting a chase scene

00:13:58.170 --> 00:14:01.605
through the streets of
Tangier, doubling for Havana--

00:14:01.605 --> 00:14:03.480
which, by the way, I
just said that sentence,

00:14:03.480 --> 00:14:06.690
and it sounds awesome.

00:14:06.690 --> 00:14:09.150
And that day, it poured
rain all morning long.

00:14:09.150 --> 00:14:11.032
And we were in
two inches of rain

00:14:11.032 --> 00:14:12.240
in the middle of this Medina.

00:14:12.240 --> 00:14:14.190
We had like, 200 extras.

00:14:14.190 --> 00:14:15.540
It was a big day.

00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:18.060
And it didn't stop
raining for the first four

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:18.960
hours of the day.

00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:21.315
So we just lost a
whole bunch of time.

00:14:21.315 --> 00:14:23.940
The sun finally came out, but we
had lost the ability to shoot.

00:14:23.940 --> 00:14:25.732
Because we were at the
end of the schedule,

00:14:25.732 --> 00:14:28.650
and we were out of
things to shoot that

00:14:28.650 --> 00:14:32.460
weren't basically action
scenes set in a Medina.

00:14:32.460 --> 00:14:34.830
And we were out
of space to do it.

00:14:34.830 --> 00:14:35.913
So we were sitting there.

00:14:35.913 --> 00:14:37.580
It was me and the
director, Steve Boyum.

00:14:37.580 --> 00:14:39.122
And we were trying
to figure out, OK,

00:14:39.122 --> 00:14:41.772
what can we do here
when the sun goes down?

00:14:41.772 --> 00:14:43.230
Because we've got
to keep shooting.

00:14:43.230 --> 00:14:45.563
Because we've got-- we've got
basically three days left.

00:14:45.563 --> 00:14:47.730
But we've got eight pages
still left to shoot.

00:14:47.730 --> 00:14:49.600
And the only thing
left on the schedule

00:14:49.600 --> 00:14:51.600
that we hadn't shot yet
that we meant to pick up

00:14:51.600 --> 00:14:54.660
in other places, but it kept
dropping off of our schedule,

00:14:54.660 --> 00:14:57.060
was this little
moment in Episode 2

00:14:57.060 --> 00:14:59.550
where they parachute
into a place

00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:01.680
and they roll over
in a parachute.

00:15:01.680 --> 00:15:05.610
And we had this Medina set.

00:15:05.610 --> 00:15:09.840
And we had, like, was it two
eighths of a page of you guys

00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:12.360
landing in a parachute
and rolling over.

00:15:12.360 --> 00:15:14.070
And so we decided, OK.

00:15:14.070 --> 00:15:15.780
All we need to do
is we need someone

00:15:15.780 --> 00:15:18.720
to go out and find us like,
four feet square of AstroTurf.

00:15:18.720 --> 00:15:21.420
And we can shoot this scene
in the middle of the Medina.

00:15:21.420 --> 00:15:22.480
We did that.

00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:24.660
But then we also
didn't realize by doing

00:15:24.660 --> 00:15:28.070
that in the middle of the
Medina in Tangier, which is--

00:15:28.070 --> 00:15:29.250
it's a safe place.

00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:32.200
But you know, you try not
to get people riled up.

00:15:32.200 --> 00:15:34.200
But they were-- some
people were very displeased

00:15:34.200 --> 00:15:35.790
that we had a man and
a woman rolling around

00:15:35.790 --> 00:15:37.500
in a parachute in the
middle of a Medina.

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:39.510
So it got to be a very--

00:15:39.510 --> 00:15:40.890
it was a very interesting night.

00:15:40.890 --> 00:15:41.807
But I'll never forget.

00:15:41.807 --> 00:15:44.540
You look at the cut of the
episode, and you don't realize,

00:15:44.540 --> 00:15:48.150
oh we shot that like, this far
away from a lamb on a spit.

00:15:48.150 --> 00:15:50.173
When a romantic
scene of you guys

00:15:50.173 --> 00:15:51.340
rolling around on AstroTurf.

00:15:51.340 --> 00:15:51.720
Yeah.

00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:52.512
SOFIA PERNAS: Yeah.

00:15:52.512 --> 00:15:53.250
That was nuts.

00:15:53.250 --> 00:15:54.708
JOSH LANZET: From
a lamb on a spit?

00:15:54.708 --> 00:15:56.083
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah
because that's

00:15:56.083 --> 00:15:57.190
part of the other episode.

00:15:57.190 --> 00:15:58.030
JOSH LANZET: Oh.

00:15:58.030 --> 00:15:58.530
Of course.

00:15:58.530 --> 00:15:59.010
Obviously.

00:15:59.010 --> 00:16:00.060
I don't know why I
didn't think that.

00:16:00.060 --> 00:16:02.850
STEVEN SCAIA: We had to take
the stand that we were shooting,

00:16:02.850 --> 00:16:04.860
this sort of like-- it
was like a market set.

00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:08.010
We stripped it down, stapled
the four feet of AstroTurf

00:16:08.010 --> 00:16:09.660
that our prop guy
had found somewhere

00:16:09.660 --> 00:16:12.565
in the streets of Morocco,
brought it back, set it up--

00:16:12.565 --> 00:16:14.940
SOFIA PERNAS: And every time
I would rest my head on what

00:16:14.940 --> 00:16:17.220
I thought was just
beautiful, lush grass,

00:16:17.220 --> 00:16:19.285
there would be a needle
in the back of my head.

00:16:19.285 --> 00:16:21.508
Where he stapled the AstroTurf.

00:16:21.508 --> 00:16:23.550
And I'd be like, Matt,
just let me down easy, OK?

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:24.822
Just let me down easy.

00:16:24.822 --> 00:16:27.075
I don't want a lobotomy today.

00:16:27.075 --> 00:16:29.700
JOSH LANZET: Now you said there
was something at the Colosseum?

00:16:29.700 --> 00:16:30.492
STEVEN SCAIA: Yeah.

00:16:30.492 --> 00:16:32.910
So we got to shoot
outside the Colosseum.

00:16:32.910 --> 00:16:34.590
And it was this
amazing location.

00:16:34.590 --> 00:16:36.930
There's this park overlooking
the Colosseum that's--

00:16:36.930 --> 00:16:39.450
I've never seen it in a
movie or a TV show before.

00:16:39.450 --> 00:16:42.000
But it's this amazing-- it's
like a dog park in Rome.

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:43.090
Because they don't care.

00:16:43.090 --> 00:16:44.770
It's just like, this is
where we walk our dog.

00:16:44.770 --> 00:16:45.270
MATT BARR: It's incredible.

00:16:45.270 --> 00:16:46.228
STEVEN SCAIA: Whatever.

00:16:46.228 --> 00:16:48.790
And so we had
locked the location.

00:16:48.790 --> 00:16:50.550
And we were going to
shoot it the next day

00:16:50.550 --> 00:16:53.740
where Danny and
Father Chuck were

00:16:53.740 --> 00:16:56.220
going to have a nice scene.

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:58.680
MATT BARR: I just remember
we had lost that location.

00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:00.510
And the next day,
we had had it back.

00:17:00.510 --> 00:17:03.360
And I was like, our
producer, Irene, I said--

00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:03.980
yeah.

00:17:03.980 --> 00:17:05.400
I said, how did you swing it?

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:08.369
She goes, she goes,
don't ask me that.

00:17:08.369 --> 00:17:11.270
Just continue with your day.

00:17:11.270 --> 00:17:11.940
Shit.

00:17:11.940 --> 00:17:13.290
STEVEN SCAIA: And that
was the kind of thing

00:17:13.290 --> 00:17:14.790
we were up against
the entire time

00:17:14.790 --> 00:17:18.089
where, I guess the mayor
of Rome had declared

00:17:18.089 --> 00:17:20.915
that all public
parks in the district

00:17:20.915 --> 00:17:23.040
were closed because it was
the worst weather they'd

00:17:23.040 --> 00:17:24.599
had in six years.

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:26.920
And all of the old
trees were falling down.

00:17:26.920 --> 00:17:31.435
But we were happy to go in and,
you know, take the trees out,

00:17:31.435 --> 00:17:32.310
clean it up for them.

00:17:32.310 --> 00:17:36.330
Like guys, we'll leave that park
nicer than when we got there.

00:17:36.330 --> 00:17:37.480
And they're like, no.

00:17:37.480 --> 00:17:39.240
Za parks, they're all closed.

00:17:39.240 --> 00:17:39.743
And--

00:17:39.743 --> 00:17:41.243
MATT BARR: He's
Italian, by the way.

00:17:41.243 --> 00:17:42.510
So it's offensive--

00:17:42.510 --> 00:17:43.530
JOSH LANZET: Spot
on It was spot on.

00:17:43.530 --> 00:17:45.072
STEVEN SCAIA: But
I will say, I don't

00:17:45.072 --> 00:17:46.320
know what happened overnight.

00:17:46.320 --> 00:17:48.977
I just know that maybe--

00:17:48.977 --> 00:17:49.560
you know what?

00:17:49.560 --> 00:17:50.955
I'm not going to say.

00:17:50.955 --> 00:17:52.353
I'm not going to guess.

00:17:52.353 --> 00:17:53.520
Because I still want to be--

00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:56.280
I want to be welcomed back
to Italy for Season 2.

00:17:56.280 --> 00:17:57.083
I just know that--

00:17:57.083 --> 00:17:59.250
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: Persuasive
people made their case.

00:17:59.250 --> 00:18:01.402
STEVEN SCAIA: It
got taken care of.

00:18:01.402 --> 00:18:02.610
JOSH LANZET: I mean, I just--

00:18:02.610 --> 00:18:04.110
I hope you're hearing
these sentences.

00:18:04.110 --> 00:18:06.277
The mayor of Rome said no,
and then all of a sudden,

00:18:06.277 --> 00:18:06.880
he said yes.

00:18:06.880 --> 00:18:10.230
I don't think people
say that ever.

00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:11.783
STEVEN SCAIA: It's
definitely-- it's

00:18:11.783 --> 00:18:13.950
a different experience than
shooting in Simi Valley,

00:18:13.950 --> 00:18:14.608
I will say.

00:18:14.608 --> 00:18:15.900
JOSH LANZET: And you know what?

00:18:15.900 --> 00:18:17.040
I think the show
could've worked there.

00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:17.990
Can I say that?

00:18:17.990 --> 00:18:18.930
I don't--

00:18:18.930 --> 00:18:20.060
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: Season 3.

00:18:20.060 --> 00:18:21.270
JOSH LANZET: Yeah, as I
was watching, I was like,

00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:23.210
let's get this to
Toronto or Atlanta.

00:18:23.210 --> 00:18:25.770
That's where this could be.

00:18:25.770 --> 00:18:28.770
Were there any challenges for
the two of you in all of this

00:18:28.770 --> 00:18:29.400
travel?

00:18:29.400 --> 00:18:32.400
Any kind of things
you didn't see coming?

00:18:32.400 --> 00:18:33.750
SOFIA PERNAS: Not dying.

00:18:33.750 --> 00:18:34.946
MATT BARR: Not dying.

00:18:34.946 --> 00:18:37.330
SOFIA PERNAS: That's
my nice answer.

00:18:37.330 --> 00:18:39.930
MATT BARR: We snuck off
to Pasitano for like,

00:18:39.930 --> 00:18:42.690
a couple days when we
had our probably two days

00:18:42.690 --> 00:18:44.050
off the whole shoot we had.

00:18:44.050 --> 00:18:46.610
And, you know, the trains,
like, finding your way

00:18:46.610 --> 00:18:47.750
around is kind of tough.

00:18:47.750 --> 00:18:50.478
So we wound up in,
like, another city.

00:18:50.478 --> 00:18:51.020
As you would.

00:18:51.020 --> 00:18:53.520
And then had to find the train
to get there and then take a,

00:18:53.520 --> 00:18:56.460
you know, a van to another
city to get a little taxi

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:57.710
to the place we were going to.

00:18:57.710 --> 00:19:00.840
So that was fun getting lost.

00:19:00.840 --> 00:19:04.893
SOFIA PERNAS: But during
shooting, do you remember?

00:19:04.893 --> 00:19:05.810
I don't even remember.

00:19:05.810 --> 00:19:06.842
It's like, I was wiped.

00:19:06.842 --> 00:19:08.550
STEVEN SCAIA: My
favorite part about that

00:19:08.550 --> 00:19:10.800
was you guys pretending like
you weren't getting hurt.

00:19:10.800 --> 00:19:14.030
Like, it was-- look,
it was grueling.

00:19:14.030 --> 00:19:15.030
The days were long.

00:19:15.030 --> 00:19:18.180
And there was a lot of running
around, no matter where

00:19:18.180 --> 00:19:19.717
we were in the world.

00:19:19.717 --> 00:19:21.550
And each of them would
pull that move where,

00:19:21.550 --> 00:19:24.540
it was your knee and your leg.

00:19:24.540 --> 00:19:27.200
They would show up on
set a little bit limpy.

00:19:27.200 --> 00:19:29.147
And they'd be like,
nah, it's fine.

00:19:29.147 --> 00:19:29.730
Let's do this.

00:19:29.730 --> 00:19:30.080
Let's do it.

00:19:30.080 --> 00:19:30.570
It's fine.

00:19:30.570 --> 00:19:31.440
SOFIA PERNAS: I like this
just hanging off of my hip.

00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:33.150
STEVEN SCAIA: I just need a
little ice and about 15 Advil.

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:33.840
We'll do it.

00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:35.190
It's like they were
like old stunt men

00:19:35.190 --> 00:19:36.900
by the time we were
done with this thing.

00:19:36.900 --> 00:19:39.150
MATT BARR: I remember thinking
I was hiding that well.

00:19:39.150 --> 00:19:41.340
STEVEN SCAIA: No, you
were terrible at it.

00:19:41.340 --> 00:19:43.050
SOFIA PERNAS: There was
one-- there was one day where

00:19:43.050 --> 00:19:43.967
we were in the Medina.

00:19:43.967 --> 00:19:45.660
I had no idea how Stephen Boyum.

00:19:45.660 --> 00:19:46.500
Did it.

00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.920
Well not-- well he was
a director of ours.

00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:52.780
But anyway, so it was packed.

00:19:52.780 --> 00:19:53.680
It was crazy.

00:19:53.680 --> 00:19:55.350
And then I'm
pouring tea with one

00:19:55.350 --> 00:19:56.850
of our castmates, Katja Winter.

00:19:56.850 --> 00:19:58.580
And it's like, you
know, a long pour tea.

00:19:58.580 --> 00:20:00.663
And then all of a sudden,
you just hear screaming.

00:20:00.663 --> 00:20:01.388
From nowhere.

00:20:01.388 --> 00:20:03.180
And I was like, wait,
that's not us, is it?

00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:05.490
That's not-- that's
not-- there's no way.

00:20:05.490 --> 00:20:06.720
And then we look over.

00:20:06.720 --> 00:20:08.820
And there's just a
riot breaking out.

00:20:08.820 --> 00:20:11.050
And Matt-- I think you're
in the middle of it.

00:20:11.050 --> 00:20:12.590
Well, you were
shooting your scene.

00:20:12.590 --> 00:20:13.257
MATT BARR: Yeah.

00:20:13.257 --> 00:20:15.590
JOSH LANZET: I was
taking a break.

00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:17.810
And I was like, this is
what happens when I leave.

00:20:17.810 --> 00:20:18.796
A riot.

00:20:18.796 --> 00:20:19.870
A riot breaks out.

00:20:19.870 --> 00:20:20.760
But it was nuts.

00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:21.570
MATT BARR: I just
thought the people who

00:20:21.570 --> 00:20:24.000
were directing the extras
was like, doing a great job.

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:25.792
Like, look at these
guys-- these kids are--

00:20:25.792 --> 00:20:26.667
STEVEN SCAIA: Use it!

00:20:26.667 --> 00:20:27.740
SOFIA PERNAS: Clamoring.

00:20:27.740 --> 00:20:29.310
MATT BARR: Everyone's
so into this.

00:20:29.310 --> 00:20:29.760
JOSH LANZET: And
all of a sudden,

00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:31.140
a riot appeared in the script.

00:20:31.140 --> 00:20:32.057
And it all made sense.

00:20:32.057 --> 00:20:33.140
STEVEN SCAIA: Looks great.

00:20:33.140 --> 00:20:34.320
JOSH LANZET: No, I'm sure.

00:20:34.320 --> 00:20:36.420
STEVEN SCAIA: You can't--
you can't pay for that.

00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:37.950
JOSH LANZET: Certainly not.

00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:40.117
So, you were saying
that they got injured.

00:20:40.117 --> 00:20:41.700
So there were a lot
of stunts in this.

00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:45.123
Were you doing most
of your own stunts?

00:20:45.123 --> 00:20:45.790
MATT BARR: Yeah.

00:20:45.790 --> 00:20:46.210
Yeah.

00:20:46.210 --> 00:20:47.127
SOFIA PERNAS: We were.

00:20:47.127 --> 00:20:50.800
But the really cool stuff, my
stunt double, Zandara Kennedy.

00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:53.170
I mean, that girl is just--

00:20:53.170 --> 00:20:54.070
she's an Avenger.

00:20:54.070 --> 00:20:57.310
Ii mean, she was going
150 miles on a Ducati.

00:20:57.310 --> 00:20:58.390
And there's no way.

00:20:58.390 --> 00:21:01.580
CBS was like, you won't even
go two miles on a motorcycle.

00:21:01.580 --> 00:21:03.400
But Zandara-- of course
her name's Zandara.

00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:03.850
So.

00:21:03.850 --> 00:21:04.150
JOSH LANZET: Sure.

00:21:04.150 --> 00:21:05.120
That makes sense.

00:21:05.120 --> 00:21:07.078
MATT BARR: Sofia's being
pretty modest, really.

00:21:07.078 --> 00:21:09.100
This girl really-- she
is like half ninja.

00:21:09.100 --> 00:21:11.350
I mean, she knows martial arts.

00:21:11.350 --> 00:21:13.240
She handled-- she
did a military show,

00:21:13.240 --> 00:21:14.368
so she knows weaponry well.

00:21:14.368 --> 00:21:15.910
And it's like, I
mean, I'll be damned

00:21:15.910 --> 00:21:19.918
if she can't do everything that,
you know, they want her to do.

00:21:19.918 --> 00:21:21.460
MATTHEW FEDERMAN:
There was one night

00:21:21.460 --> 00:21:24.340
where we had a big fight
scene, in 103, that big fight

00:21:24.340 --> 00:21:25.510
scene in the tea thing.

00:21:25.510 --> 00:21:27.173
And we were like--

00:21:27.173 --> 00:21:29.590
they said, like, we had like,
five hours of shooting left,

00:21:29.590 --> 00:21:31.960
but like, an hour
to shoot it in.

00:21:31.960 --> 00:21:34.900
And every one of them had a
fight scene within that fight

00:21:34.900 --> 00:21:37.253
scene that-- because
it was basically

00:21:37.253 --> 00:21:39.420
four of them going to battle
against the entire room

00:21:39.420 --> 00:21:40.570
full of people.

00:21:40.570 --> 00:21:43.480
And every one of them,
you watch Matt go in.

00:21:43.480 --> 00:21:46.300
And he just like, nails this
really complicated fight

00:21:46.300 --> 00:21:48.250
with five guys at the same time.

00:21:48.250 --> 00:21:50.540
And a hookah pipe that
breaks in the middle of it.

00:21:50.540 --> 00:21:51.865
And it was like, wow.

00:21:51.865 --> 00:21:52.490
He nailed that.

00:21:52.490 --> 00:21:53.150
And then, OK.

00:21:53.150 --> 00:21:53.590
Let's do it again.

00:21:53.590 --> 00:21:54.250
He nails it again.

00:21:54.250 --> 00:21:54.625
It was like, oh.

00:21:54.625 --> 00:21:55.583
And then he comes back.

00:21:55.583 --> 00:21:56.868
He's like, did my part.

00:21:56.868 --> 00:21:58.160
And then she's like, all right.

00:21:58.160 --> 00:21:59.183
I'm going in.

00:21:59.183 --> 00:22:00.850
One after another,
they just all went in

00:22:00.850 --> 00:22:01.750
and they just nailed it.

00:22:01.750 --> 00:22:03.667
And it's like, wow, this
show would really not

00:22:03.667 --> 00:22:05.443
be makeable without
this group of people,

00:22:05.443 --> 00:22:07.360
if you had, you know,
any other set of actors.

00:22:07.360 --> 00:22:08.980
STEVEN SCAIA: I think
our directors were always

00:22:08.980 --> 00:22:10.857
surprised because they
would read the scripts

00:22:10.857 --> 00:22:12.190
and see how ambitious they were.

00:22:12.190 --> 00:22:16.630
And then they would show up like
a good guest director trying

00:22:16.630 --> 00:22:17.890
to make it easier.

00:22:17.890 --> 00:22:19.137
And we'd be like, no, no, no.

00:22:19.137 --> 00:22:20.470
That's not "Blood and Treasure."

00:22:20.470 --> 00:22:22.270
We have to make this harder.

00:22:22.270 --> 00:22:23.740
And they would get into it.

00:22:23.740 --> 00:22:26.710
And then they would see these
guys on set thinking, OK so,

00:22:26.710 --> 00:22:29.943
we'll use the stunt doubles
for all of the big action.

00:22:29.943 --> 00:22:31.360
We'll punch in for
some close ups.

00:22:31.360 --> 00:22:34.330
And we would just laugh and
be like, sure, sure, sure.

00:22:34.330 --> 00:22:36.953
Why don't we just do one run
through with our actors first?

00:22:36.953 --> 00:22:38.620
Just sort of like,
just to warm them up.

00:22:38.620 --> 00:22:42.740
And they'd see you guys do it at
full speed, completely capable.

00:22:42.740 --> 00:22:45.520
And then they would just look
at the two stunt, you know,

00:22:45.520 --> 00:22:48.472
the two stunt people, and
be like, Robert and Zandara,

00:22:48.472 --> 00:22:50.180
you guys can just hang
here for a minute.

00:22:50.180 --> 00:22:52.690
And then they would just
sit in costume and chairs

00:22:52.690 --> 00:22:54.728
while you guys did the
entire thing yourselves.

00:22:54.728 --> 00:22:55.770
SOFIA PERNAS: It was fun.

00:22:55.770 --> 00:22:56.730
It was fun.

00:22:56.730 --> 00:22:59.650
It was also like, there was
one fight scene where it

00:22:59.650 --> 00:23:01.240
was, you know, girl and girl.

00:23:01.240 --> 00:23:03.020
We were just going at it.

00:23:03.020 --> 00:23:05.550
It was-- well--

00:23:05.550 --> 00:23:06.675
MATTHEW FEDERMAN: Language.

00:23:06.675 --> 00:23:07.633
JOSH LANZET: All right.

00:23:09.780 --> 00:23:12.890
I love just watching
Matt's face during that.

00:23:12.890 --> 00:23:14.380
He went on a journey.

00:23:14.380 --> 00:23:16.900
STEVEN SCAIA: This
show has everything.

00:23:16.900 --> 00:23:19.820
SOFIA PERNAS: You guys,
please watch 21st.

00:23:19.820 --> 00:23:22.022
But yeah, it was a really
intense fight scene.

00:23:22.022 --> 00:23:23.980
And I remember the stunt
double I was fighting.

00:23:23.980 --> 00:23:25.022
Her name was [INAUDIBLE].

00:23:25.022 --> 00:23:26.170
She was a ninja.

00:23:26.170 --> 00:23:28.660
But there was-- it starts off
with her doing this flying

00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:29.200
kick at me.

00:23:29.200 --> 00:23:31.330
And she's like, I don't
know how to sell this.

00:23:31.330 --> 00:23:35.020
Because it's a kick in mid
air and I'm hitting you.

00:23:35.020 --> 00:23:36.340
I was like, just kick me.

00:23:36.340 --> 00:23:37.910
Just do it.

00:23:37.910 --> 00:23:38.410
Just do it.

00:23:38.410 --> 00:23:39.702
And she was like, are you sure?

00:23:39.702 --> 00:23:41.380
I was like, just do it.

00:23:41.380 --> 00:23:42.340
We have no time.

00:23:42.340 --> 00:23:43.298
And then she kicked me.

00:23:43.298 --> 00:23:45.053
And I was like, oh my god.

00:23:45.053 --> 00:23:46.510
You like, drove the--

00:23:46.510 --> 00:23:48.750
the lungs-- just the
air out of my body.

00:23:48.750 --> 00:23:50.830
But and then it was a
five minute fight scene.

00:23:50.830 --> 00:23:52.663
STEVEN SCAIA: By the
way, that's in the cut,

00:23:52.663 --> 00:23:54.773
because it looks awesome.

00:23:54.773 --> 00:23:56.440
SOFIA PERNAS: She's
a tae kwon do champ.

00:23:56.440 --> 00:23:57.350
I can tell you.

00:23:57.350 --> 00:23:58.075
Yeah.

00:23:58.075 --> 00:23:59.950
MATT BARR: There's a
scene where I'm giving--

00:23:59.950 --> 00:24:02.162
I'm stabbing Sofia in
the arm with a little--

00:24:02.162 --> 00:24:03.370
I don't want to say too much.

00:24:03.370 --> 00:24:06.010
A little thing to save her life.

00:24:06.010 --> 00:24:06.900
And so, you know, I--

00:24:06.900 --> 00:24:07.450
MATTHEW FEDERMAN:
Well if you say less,

00:24:07.450 --> 00:24:08.230
it's going to
actually be weirder--

00:24:08.230 --> 00:24:08.380
MATT BARR: Yeah.

00:24:08.380 --> 00:24:09.020
That's right.

00:24:09.020 --> 00:24:09.380
Yeah.

00:24:09.380 --> 00:24:10.672
That's what we're trying to do.

00:24:10.672 --> 00:24:12.588
STEVEN SCAIA: Guys this
show has everything.

00:24:12.588 --> 00:24:13.880
JOSH LANZET: It's in the pilot.

00:24:13.880 --> 00:24:15.592
MATT BARR: So like,
after 10 takes,

00:24:15.592 --> 00:24:17.050
